## Context

- **Task 1310 (P4) completed**: TS risk gene expression across interneuron subtypes
  - 19/20 risk genes profiled (HDC too sparse, filtered during QC)
  - All 9 core risk genes significantly differentially expressed across subtypes (KW p<1e-5)
  - NRXN1 massively enriched in CR interneurons (FC=1.43, p=2.6e-65, 78% expressing)
  - KMT2C enriched in PV_FSI (p=1.65e-6), SMARCA2 in PTHLH (p=2.55e-5)
  - FLT3 (GWAS) enriched in SST_PLTS (p=9.58e-14)
  - De novo WES genes (PPP5C/EXOC1/GXYLT1) trend toward ChAT_CIN but only 15 cells — underpowered
  - Output: risk_gene_expression.csv, risk_gene_enrichment_stats.csv, 5 figures

- **Task 1312 (P4) completed**: Interneuron subtype transcriptomic signatures + pathway enrichment
  - Wilcoxon rank-sum DE on full 16,609-gene atlas (13,567 interneurons, 5 subtypes)
  - All subtypes validated: PVALB top for PV_FSI, SST for SST_PLTS, CALB2 for CR, RELN/LAMP5 for NPY_NGF
  - Pathway enrichment (GO/KEGG/Reactome): PV_FSI=32, SST_PLTS=78, NPY_NGF=133, CR=66, PTHLH=1 terms
  - Notable findings: SST_PLTS enriched in KEGG neurodegeneration pathways; CR markers show NLRP3 inflammasome signal
  - Created RD task #1462 to evaluate SST neurodegeneration + CR neuroimmune findings
  - Output: interneuron_subtype_markers.csv (500 genes), pathway_enrichment_results.csv (310 terms)

- **Known issues** (carried forward):
  - ChAT_CIN only 15 cells (underpowered) — HVG-based scoring misses many
  - TH+ interneurons not recovered (TH not in HVGs)
  - 39.4% ambiguous classifications from HVG-subset scoring
  - pandas 3.0 ArrowStringArray issue — must set pd.options.future.infer_string=False
  - anndata backed mode indexing broken (backed_csr_matrix lacks _validate_indices)

